President Obama has declared an emergency in the state of Connecticut due to severe winter storm conditions. This declaration allows the Department of Homeland Security and FEMA to coordinate relief efforts and provide assistance to alleviate the hardships caused by the emergency. FEMA is authorized to mobilize resources and equipment as needed to mitigate the impacts of the emergency. The federal assistance will be provided for a period of 48 hours and will be funded at 75 percent federal funding. Albert Lewis has been named as the Federal Coordinating Officer for federal recovery operations in the affected area.